      try{Typekit.load();}catch(e){}   
    %link{:href => "../examples.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
  %body
    #header
      %h1 Earth's Surface Temperature: Years 500-2009
    #intro
      %p Can you change the scales to make it appear that global temperature is not increasing?
    #chart
    #description
      %h2 About the Graph
      %ul
        %li Drag on the canvas to translate/pan the graph.
        %li double-click on the canvas to zoom in
        %li shift-double-click on the canvas to zoom out
        %li Drag on one of the X or Y axis numeric labels to re-scale that axis
        %li click on a data point to select it
        %li drag a selected data point to change it's value
        %li enter the delete or backspace key to delete a selected data point
        %li drag a selected data point to change it's value
        %li hold the ALT/Option key down and click an empty area of the graph to add a data point
      %h2 About the Data
      %p
        The data are derived from
        %a{:href => "http://climexp.knmi.nl/data/isst_mann.dat"} Mann's reconstruction of Earth's surface temperature from 500 to 2009
        %p References:
        %ul
          %li 
            %a{:href => "http://climexp.knmi.nl/data/isst_mann.dat"} SST [K] Global SST reconstruction data
          %li 
            %a{:href => "http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/paleo/pubs/mann2009b/mann2009b.html"} Global Signatures and Dynamical Origins of the Little Ice Age and Medieval Climate Anomaly
            %em
              (NOAA Paleoclimatology site)
          %li 
            %a{:href => "http://www.meteo.psu.edu/~mann/shared/articles/MannetalScience09.pdf"} Global Signatures and Dynamical Origins of the Little Ice Age and Medieval Climate Anomaly 
            %em
              (pdf of original paper)
          %li 
            %a{:href => "http://climexp.knmi.nl/getindices.cgi?RapidData/sst_mann+Mann_global_SST+i+someone@somewhere+1"} Time series annual Mann global SST
          %li
            %a{:href => "http://seaice.apl.washington.edu/Papers/JonesEtal99-SAT150.pdf"} Jones et al., 1999, Surface Air Temperature and its Changes over the Past 150 Years
      %p
        There's still a bug where if you scale an axis once, you
        can then translate/pan around but if you scale the same axis
        a second time when you next try and translate/pan the result
        of the first axis re-scale will re-appear. This bug also
        appears if you re-scale the axes and then add a new data
        point.
